item.description:
Data Model The following pseudo code can explain the git data model clearly.
Firstly, we will talk about the three models in git.
// a file is a set of data type blob = array&lt;byte&gt; // a directory which concludes files and directories type tree = map&lt;string, tree | blob&gt; // every commit concludes a parent, metadata and top tree type commit = struct { parent: array&lt;commit&gt; author: string message: string snapshot: tree } How should we understand the bolb, tree and commit?
